	(203, 1, '2015-03-05 03:04:19', '2015-03-05 03:04:19', '<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(&#39;<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/cki-template11-headers-api.jpg&#39;);"> \r\n	<header>\r\n	    <h1>How to Use Our Data API</h1>\r\n	    <hr>\r\n	</header>\r\n</section>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n    <section class="post standard">\r\n        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n            <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h2>Introduction</h2>\r\n                <hr>\r\n            </header>\r\n            <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                <p>Before you can access the API data, you will first need to get a registration key that you will need to use on all of your requests. <a href="<?php echo home_url(); ?>/api-registration">Click here</a> to get your registration key.</p>\r\n                <p>To gain access to raw information regarding the locations, dimensions, components, and scores affiliated with each Measure (U.S. Measurements or World Measurements), please use one of the following URL use cases.</p>\r\n            </article>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n    <section class="post standard">\r\n        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n            <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h2>Resources</h2>\r\n                <hr>\r\n            </header>\r\n            <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                <table>\r\n                    <tbody>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <th>Resources</th>\r\n                            <th>Description</th>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/locations/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/locations/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <strong>Locations</strong><br>\r\n                                    Returns a list of all states or nations included in the Quality of Life Measures.\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/dimensionlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/dimensionlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <strong>Dimensions</strong><br>\r\n                                Returns a list of the dimensions of quality of life measure, which are shared by the U.S. and World Measurements.\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/componentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/componentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <strong>Components</strong><br>\r\n                                Returns a list of all components (and their parent dimensions) included in the U.S. and World Measurements.\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/subcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/subcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <strong>Sub-Components</strong><br>\r\n                                Returns a list of all sub-components (and their parent components) included in the U.S. and World Measurements.\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/subsubcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/subsubcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <strong>Sub-Sub-Components</strong>\r\n                                <br>\r\n                                Returns a list of all sub-sub-components (and their parent sub-components) included in the U.S. and World Measurements.\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                    </tbody>\r\n                </table>\r\n            </article>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n    <section class="post standard">\r\n        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n            <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h2>Scores</h2>\r\n                <hr>\r\n            </header>\r\n            <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                <table>\r\n                    <tbody>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <th>Scores</th>\r\n                            <th>Description</th>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                            <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                            <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/summary/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            <h4>World</h4>\r\n                            <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/summary/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p></td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <strong>Summary Scores</strong><br>\r\n                                Returns all states or nations, scores and rankings related with the Quality of Life Measures for the most recent year that we have data.</td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <strong>All Scores</strong><br>\r\n                                    Returns all states or nations, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, scores and rankings related with the Quality of Life Measures. Includes historical data back to 2001 for US data, and 2000 for World data.\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/dimensions/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/dimensions/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <strong>Dimension Scores</strong>\r\n                                <br>\r\n                                Returns all dimension scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Measure.</td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/components/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/components/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <strong>Component Scores</strong>\r\n                                Returns all component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Measure.\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/subcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/subcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <strong>Sub-Component Scores</strong><br>\r\n                                Returns all sub-component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Measure.\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/subsubcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/subsubcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                            <td><strong>Sub-Sub-Component Scores</strong><br>\r\n                                Returns all sub-sub-component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Measure.\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                    </tbody>\r\n                </table>\r\n            </article>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n    <section class="post standard">\r\n        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n            <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h2>Targeted Queries</h2>\r\n                <hr>\r\n            </header>\r\n            <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                <p>Generating targeted lists of specific data points is done by adding query parameters to your URL. This can allow you to specify your search criteria (ex.; locations, years, dimensions, components, etc.) and get a detailed object of that data as well as a calculated score and ranking based on the returned data.</p>\r\n                <h3>Base URLs</h3>\r\n                <table>\r\n                    <tbody>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>U.S.</td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <p>This call will return all states, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, and all of the scores related to the Quality of Life U.S. Measurements. Includes historical data back to 2001.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>World</td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.connxt.net/api/index.php/int/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <p>This call will return all countries, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, and all of the scores related to the Quality of Life World Measurements. Includes historical data back to 2000.\r\n                                </p>\r\n                            </td>\r\n                        </tr>\r\n                    </tbody>\r\n                </table>\r\n                <h3>Parameters</h3>\r\n                <table>\r\n                    <tbody>\r\n                        <tr>\r\n                            <td>locations</td>\r\n                            <td>\r\n                                Returns all of the data for the individual states passed in on the request. Also compares the scores of the returned states and ranks them accordingly.<p></p>\r\n                                <p>States and countries are passed in as a pipe-delimited list