	(209, 1, '2015-03-05 03:05:07', '2015-03-05 03:05:07', '<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(&#39;<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/cki-template11-headers-faq.jpg&#39;);">\r\n    <header>\r\n        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>\r\n        <hr>\r\n    </header>\r\n</section>\r\n<div id="content" class="row">\r\n    <a name="initiative"></a>\r\n    <section class="post standard">\r\n        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n            <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h2 id="project">Project</h2>\r\n                <hr>\r\n            </header>\r\n            <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h3>Why explore The Quality of Life Measures?</h3>\r\n                <p>By facilitating an informed discussion about the Quality of Life Measures , assessing its key components, and pursuing research on its key drivers, the hope is to learn more about how to improve quality of life for society at large.</p>\r\n                <p>The concept of the Quality of Life Measures includes both short-term (happiness) and long-term (life satisfaction) components. Our analysis yields five dimensions that are central to quality of life across time, localities, and culture:</p>\r\n                <ol>\r\n                    <li>Opportunity</li>\r\n                    <li>Health &amp; Environment</li>\r\n                    <li>Freedom</li>\r\n                    <li>Community &amp; Relationships</li>\r\n                    <li>Living Standard</li>\r\n                    <li>Peace &amp; Security</li>\r\n                </ol>\r\n                <p>Learn more about the six dimensions <a href="<?php echo home_url(); ?>/constructing-the-measures"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">here</span></a>.</p>\r\n                <h3>How is the Quality of Life Measures relevant to me?</h3>\r\n                <p>Whether you are a scholar, a layman thinker or an involved citizen, the Quality of Life Measures has something valuable to offer you. The goal is to spark an informed and thoughtful dialogue on quality of life and its key drivers. The datasets are publicly available, and we encourage other researchers to use the data to provide feedback and build on the growing body of literature in this important field. For researchers and others alike, the hope is that the data and analysis help to foster a discussion on the drivers of quality of life and, ultimately, improve the lives of individuals and their communities.</p>\r\n            </article>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n    <a name="indices"></a>\r\n    <section class="post standard">\r\n        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n            <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h2 id="indices">FAQ</h2>\r\n                <hr>\r\n            </header>\r\n            <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h3 id="question_1_faqs" class="question">Can you support my research project?</h3>\r\n                <p id="answer_1_faqs" class="answers">More information forthcoming</p>\r\n\r\n                <h3 id="question_2_faqs" class="question">How do you measure quality of life?</h3>\r\n                <p id="answer_2_faqs" class="answers">Researchers have developed several ways of measuring quality of life, from public surveys to monitoring social media, each with its own set of advantages and drawbacks. The Quality of Life Measures looks at nearly fifty different indicators across six dimensions. These indicators describe the environment in which more people are likely to say they are happier and have more life satisfaction. These indicators are turned into scores, which are then aggregated into a composite score for each dimension and for the Quality of Life Measure overall to identify the best (and worst) places to live. These indicators are turned into scores, which are then aggregated into a composite score for each dimension and for quality of life measure overall.</p>\r\n                \r\n                <h3 id="question_3_faqs" class="question">Why six dimensions of Quality of Life Measures?</h3>\r\n                <p id="answer_3_faqs" class="answers">The six dimensions of the Quality of Life Measures arose from a meta-analysis of the empirical literature and a statistical analysis of the World Values Survey.  The analysis identified six groups of variables that were highly correlated with self-reported happiness and life satisfaction. The selection of these groups was bolstered by previous findings in the academic literature.</p>\r\n                \r\n                <h3 id="question_4_faqs" class="question">Where does the data come from?</h3>\r\n                <p id="answer_4_faqs" class="answers">The data in the Measures of Quality of Life comes from third-party sources that are employed in academic work. The data originate primarily from governments or respected non-governmental or international institutions. At the worldwide level, for example, much data comes from the World Banks World Governance Indicators, while at the U.S.-level much data comes from the Census.  For a full listing of data sources, see the Sources section of the full <a href="<?php echo home_url(); ?>/get-the-data">report</a>.</p>\r\n                \r\n                <h3 id="question_5_faqs" class="question">Who produces the Measures of Quality of Life?</h3>\r\n                <p id="answer_5_faqs" class="answers">The Measures of Quality of Life are produced by The Baugh Center\'s research team and then reviewed by the Advisory Board and scholars across the world.</p>\r\n                \r\n                <h3 id="question_6_faqs" class="question">What countries does the World Measures of Quality of Life cover?</h3>\r\n                <p id="answer_6_faqs" class="answers">The World Measures of Quality of Life covers every country for which enough data could be obtained to produce a score according to our methodology: 143 countries in all. To learn more, please see the <a href="<?php echo home_url(); ?>/constructing-the-measures/#statistical_analysis">methodology</a> section.</p>\r\n                \r\n                <h3 id="question_7_faqs" class="question">How do the measures take changes over time into consideration?</h3>\r\n                <p id="answer_7_faqs" class="answers">It is possible that the composition of the measures will change, either because of changes in the underlying understanding of Quality of Life or because of changes in data availability. The intention in that case will be to release an entirely new dataset, with changes applied retroactively, to ensure comparability over time.</p>\r\n                \r\n                <h3 id="question_8_faqs" class="question">How often is the data updated?</h3>\r\n                <p id="answer_8_faqs" class="answers">Most of the source data is released no more than once a year. The measures will therefore be updated on an annual basis.</p>\r\n            </article>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n    <a name="components"></a>\r\n    <section class="post standard">\r\n        <div class="row clearfix">\r\n            <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h2 id="components">Components</h2>\r\n                <hr>\r\n            </header>\r\n            <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                <h3>Components in the Quality of Life Measures</h3>\r\n                <h4>Opportunity</h4>\r\n                <p>Poverty<br>\r\n                Employment<br>\r\n                Community Vitality<br>\r\n                Entrepreneurship</p>\r\n                <h4>Health &amp; Environment</h4>\r\n                <p>Physical Health<br>\r\n                Mental &amp; Emotional Health<br>\r\n                Environmental Health</p>\r\n                <h4>Freedom</h4>\r\n                <p>Civil Liberties<br>\r\n                Religious Freedom<br>\r\n                Political Freedom<br>\r\n                Economic Freedom<br>\r\n                Perception of Freedom</p>\r\n                <h4>Community &amp; Relationships</h4>\r\n                <p>Community Life<br>\r\n                Family Life</p>\r\n                <h4>Living Standard</h4>\r\n                <p>Current Living Standard<br>\r\n                Improvement in Living Standard</p>\r\n                <h4>Peace &amp; Security</h4>\r\n                <p>Violence &amp; Ethnic Warfare<br>\r\n                Human Rights Violations<br>\r\n                Law &amp; Order<br>\r\n                Trust in National Institutions<br>\r\n                Corruption in Business &amp; Government<br>\r\n                Bureaucracy Quality</p>\r\n                <h3>Components in the U.S. Measures of Quality of Life</h3>\r\n                <h4>Opportunity</h4>\r\n                <p>Poverty<br>\r\n                Employment<br>\r\n                Community Vitality<br>\r\n                Education</p>\r\n                <h4>Health &amp; Environment</h4>\r\n                <p>Physical Health<br>\r\n                Mental &amp; Emotional Health<br>\r\n                Environmental Health</p>\r\n                <h4>Freedom</h4>\r\n                <p>Personal Freedom<br>\r\n                Economic Freedom</p>\r\n                <h4>Community &amp; Relationships</h4>\r\n                <p>Community Life<br>\r\n                Family Life</p>\r\n                <h4>Living Standard</h4>\r\n                <p>Current Living Standard<br>\r\n                Improvement in Living Standard</p>\r\n                <h4>Peace &amp; Security</h4>\r\n                <p>Violent Crime Rate<br>\r\n                Property Crime Rate<br>\r\n                Safe Walking at Night<br>\r\n                Trust in Neighbors</p>\r\n            </article>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n</div>', 'FAQS', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'faqs', '', '', '2016-03-09 22:45:42', '2016-03-09 22:45:42', '', 0, 'http://localhost/life-measures-wordpress/?page_id=209', 0, 'page', '', 0),
	(211, 1, '2015-03-05 03:05:23', '2015-03-05 03:05:23', '<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(&#39;<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/cki-template11-headers-getdata.jpg&#39;);">\r\n    <header>\r\n        <h1>Download and Interact with the Projects Data</h1>\r\n        <hr>\r\n    </header>\r\n</section>\r\n<div id="content" class="row">\r\n    <a name="the-data-for-the-indices-of-well-being-are-available-in-four-different-sets-to-suit-different-research-needs"></a>\r\n    <section class="post box post-347 standard_post  large-6 medium-6 small-12 columns">\r\n        <div class="border row clearfix">\r\n            <header>\r\n                <h2>The data for the Quality of Life Measures are available in three different sets to suit different research needs.</h2>\r\n            </header>\r\n            <article>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>The Standard dataset interpolates missing scores between data points, but it does not back-fill or forward-fill missing values.</li>\r\n                    <li>The Chain-linked dataset uses chain-linking to create a series for overall Quality of Life and each of the dimensions appropriate for time-series analysis.</li>\r\n                    <li>The Raw dataset provides all input data used to create, with no alterations.</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n                <p>In addition, the data can be downloaded through a REST-ful API, which allows for the creation of custom subsets of the Completed dataset.</p>\r\n            </article>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </section>                 \r\n    <a name="data-sets"></a>\r\n    <section class="post box data_sets large-6 medium-6 columns">\r\n        <div class="border row clearfix">\r\n            <div class="data_set clearfix">\r\n                <header>\r\n                    <h2 id="us_data_sets">United States Datasets</h2>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article>\r\n                    <div class="data_set_list Standard">\r\n                        <span class="type">Standard</span>\r\n                            <span class="csv download">\r\n                                <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/us_data/StateIndexStandard.csv">CSV</a>\r\n                            </span>\r\n                        <span class="dta download">\r\n                            <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/us_data/StateIndexStandard.dta">Stata</a>\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class="data_set_list Chain-Linked">\r\n                        <span class="type">Chain-Linked</span>\r\n                        <span class="csv download">\r\n                            <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/us_data/StateIndexChained.csv">CSV</a>\r\n                        </span>\r\n                        <span class="dta download">\r\n                            <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/us_data/StateIndexChained.dta">Stata</a>\r\n                        </span>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class="data_set_list Raw">\r\n                        <span class="type">Raw</span>\r\n                        <span class="csv download">\r\n                        <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/us_data/StateIndexRaw.csv">CSV</a></span>\r\n                            <span class="dta download">\r\n                        <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/us_data/StateIndexRaw.dta">Stata</a></span>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n            <div class="data_set clearfix">\r\n                <header>\r\n                    <h2 id="world_data_sets">World Datasets</h2>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article>\r\n                    <div class="data_set_list Standard">\r\n                        <span class="type">Standard</span>\r\n                            <span class="csv download">\r\n                                <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/world_data/WorldIndexStandard.csv">CSV</a></span>\r\n                                <span class="dta download">\r\n                                <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/world_data/WorldIndexStandard.dta">Stata</a></span>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class="data_set_list Chain-Linked">\r\n                        <span class="type">Chain-Linked</span>\r\n                            <span class="csv download">\r\n                                <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/world_data/WorldIndexChained.csv">CSV</a></span>\r\n                                <span class="dta download">\r\n                                <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/world_data/WorldIndexChained.dta">Stata</a></span>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class="data_set_list Raw">\r\n                        <span class="type">Raw</span>\r\n                        <span class="csv download">\r\n                        <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/world_data/WorldIndexRaw.csv">CSV</a></span>\r\n                        <span class="dta download">\r\n                        <a target="_blank" href="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/world_data/WorldIndexRaw.dta">Stata</a></span>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <br><br>\r\n    </section>\r\n        <a name="using-the-api"></a>\r\n        <div class="row">\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n                <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                    <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns header-using-the-api">\r\n                        <h2>Using The API</h2>\r\n                        <hr>\r\n                    </header>\r\n                    <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns using-the-api" >\r\n                        <p>The Quality of Life Measures provides a REST-ful API to allow for the downloading of custom selections based on the completed dataset. Using the API, you can download a subset of countries, years, and indicators, as well as recalculate dimension and summary scores from that subset.</p>\r\n                        <p>The API returns data in the JSON format.</p>\r\n                    </article>\r\n                    <article>\r\n                        <a class="btn flat blue btn-data" href="<?php echo home_url(); ?>/api-registration">Register for the API</a>\r\n                    </article>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </section>\r\n            <a name="the-report"></a>\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n                <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                    <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns header-the-report">\r\n                        <h2>The Report</h2>\r\n                        <hr>\r\n                    </header>\r\n                    <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns the-report">\r\n                        <p>The 2014 Measures of Quality of Life presents an innovative and comprehensive picture of Quality of Life Measures throughout the world and across the 50 U.S. States.</p>\r\n                        <p>This inaugural report lays out these new measures, with comprehensive scores and rankings covering 14 years and almost 100 variables between the U.S. states and the worlds countries.</p>\r\n                    </article>\r\n                    <article>\r\n                        <a class="btn flat blue download pdf btn-data" href ="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/pdf/Well-Being_Report_Book.docx" target="_blank" style="background-image: url(&#39;<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/icons/pdf.png&#39;);">Download the Report</a>\r\n                    </article>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </section>\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        <!-- <a name="explore-the-map"></a>\r\n        <section class="post box post-365 standard_post  large-6 medium-6 columns">\r\n            <div class="border row clearfix">\r\n                <div class="content">\r\n                    <img src="<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/cki-template12-getdata-img.jpg" alt="Explore the Map">\r\n                    <header>\r\n                    </header>\r\n                    <article>\r\n                        <p>The Quality of Life Measures compiled data from all 50 states and 153 countries to determine just how well people are living worldwide.</p>\r\n                        <a class="btn flat blue " href="<?php echo home_url(); ?>/interactive-map">Explore the Map</a>\r\n                    </article>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section> -->\r\n        <!-- <a name="stats"></a>\r\n        <section class="post box stats large-6 medium-6 columns">\r\n            <div class="border row clearfix">\r\n                <ul class="stats-list">\r\n                    <li class="slide dimension border opportunity singapore">\r\n                        <div class="vertical-align">\r\n                            <div class="image-block">\r\n                                <img class=\'svg\' src=\'<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/svg/SG.svg\' alt=\'Singapore\'>                            \r\n                            </div>\r\n                            <div class="state-name"><span class="border"></span><span class="state">Singapore</span><span class="border"></span></div>\r\n                            <p><p>Singapor